CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 20, 1954, pg. 27, reads: "Repeaters - Westinghouse High School's crack basketball team won their fifth consecutive City League basketball title last Saturday at the Pitt Field House, defeating Allegheny. The team is shown in locker room moments after the win enjoying a victory celebration. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Westinghouse High School basketball team, including #19 Roosevelt "Royo" Giddens kneeling on left, #18 Tony Aullicianio and Bradford in rear, and Coach Willard Fisher seated in center, cheering in locker room after PIAA city championships playoff
